reviewText: With Madhavan being hot property in Kodambakkam ever since Alaipayuthey, his second movie was highly anticipated. But unless he selects stories and scripts that are much better than Ennavale, his stay might be a short-lived one. The movie has a familiar feel with both the story and many of the sequences reminding one of earlier movies. While his charm and enthusiasm are apparent, he is still a long way from carrying an otherwise inferior movie entirely on his thin shoulders
